    • Method Detail

      • isRedirectUrlValid

        public boolean isRedirectUrlValid(String url,
                                  T configInfo)
        Validates the provided redirect URL against the collection of valid goto URL domains found based on the configuration info.
        Parameters:
        url - The URL that needs to be validated. May be null.
        configInfo - The necessary information about the configuration to determine the collection of valid goto URL domains. May not be null.
        Returns:
        true if the provided URL is valid, false otherwise.

      • getRedirectUrl

        public String getRedirectUrl(T configInfo,
                             String gotoUrl,
                             String alternateUrl)
        Returns the appopriate redirectUrl, given the options of the provided URL and the default one, as well as a configuration. The configuration determines whether gotoUrl is valid and complies with the configuration's URL policy. If so, the gotoUrl is returned, otherwise the alternateUrl is returned. In the case where the alternateUrl is null, null is returned.
        Parameters:
        configInfo - Config in the given type which informs the collection of valid domain URLs.
        gotoUrl - The goto URL to compare against the config. If null alternateUrl will be returned.
        alternateUrl - The URL to default to. May be null.
        Returns:
        The URL to use, or null if no URL is appropriate.

      • getAndDecodeParameter

        public String getAndDecodeParameter(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request,
                                    String paramName)
        Helper function to retrieve a field from the provided request's query parameters. This exists for the old-style interfaces, and takes the parameter name as an argument also. If the queryParameters contain the "encoded" parameter, then the result is Base64 decoded before being returned.
        Parameters:
        request - Request containing the parameters to retrieve.
        paramName - The name of the parameter whose value to (possibly decode) return.
        Returns:
        The (possibly decoded) value of the paramName's key within the requests's query parameters.

      • getValueFromJson

        public String getValueFromJson(org.forgerock.json.JsonValue input,
                               String paramName)
        Helper function to retrieve a field from the provided request's JSON POST data. This exists for the new-style interfaces, and takes the parameter name as an argument also.
        Parameters:
        input - JsonValue containing the key "goto" and a paired URL.
        paramName - The key whose value to attempt to read.
        Returns:
        The String representation fo the "goto" key's value, or null.
